Some motorists can finally breathe a sigh of relief  after the Energy Department announced a 12 cents price drop from Wednesday. The price of diesel is however expected to increase by 92 cents a litre. The price of paraffin is expected to increase by 93.85 cents a litre. The Energy Department’s Robert Maake said the sanctions against Russia following that country’s latest conflict with the Ukraine has contributed to the increased price of diesel and paraffin.